      • onLogLine

        void onLogLine(java.lang.String logLine)
        A new line was read from the log

      • onStart

        void onStart()
        Capture started (vie either LogCatcher.dump(OnLogLinesListener) or LogCatcher.startCapture(OnLogLinesListener)). This method indicates that the logcat process was successfully executed and the LogCatcher instance is now reading from the log stream.

      • onFinished

        void onFinished()
        Capture finished.
        • If the capture was started via LogCatcher.dump(OnLogLinesListener), this method indicates that the end of stream was reached.
        • If the capture was started via LogCatcher.startCapture(OnLogLinesListener), this method indicates that LogCatcher.endCapture() was called.

      • onError

        void onError(java.lang.Throwable t)
        Error encountered
        Parameters:
        t - caught error either during the execution of the logcat command or while trying to read from the log stream.
